<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-12-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="941" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d941">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay.</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-12-27"><hi rend="italic">December 27,
                                    1903</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 237.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                            United States-Venezuelan claims commission which met in Caracas on June
                            1, 1903, completed its work on the 26th instant. Several claims are
                            still awaiting the umpire’s decision.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William W.
                            Russell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>